           Current Principal [theorylogo.gif] Research Activities

   Factorization formalism for decay and production of heavy quarkonia;
          renormalons in quarkonium matrix elements,^ q.v.æ.

   Large perturbative corrections in QCD, soft gluon resummation:
          applications to the top quark and SUSY pair production

   Particle cosmology
   Higgs Physics
   Lattice QCD simulations: thermodynamics, improved actions, heavy
          quarkonium decay rates, ^q.v.æ.

   Collider Physics phenomenology related to experiments at LEP, HERA,
          Fermilab, RHIC and the LHC:
          SUSY and Higgs phenomenology
          Heavy-quark production
          Inclusive and isolated photon production
          Massive lepton pair production

   Star products, Wigner Functions, Deformation Quantization, with physics
          and non-commutative geometry applications, ^q.v.æ.

   Extra Dimensional Mediation of SUSY breaking
   Spin dependence of hard scattering processes, RHIC physics
   Electroweak Symmetry Breaking induced by the QCD interaction of color
          sextet quarks

   Regge behavior of gauge theories; the Pomeron, confinement, and chiral
          symmetry in QCD, ^q.v.æ.

   Lattice regularization of gauge theories with fermions: the Standard
          Electroweak Model; tadpole improvement of lattice perturbation
          theory
          Neutrino physics

